  "prompt": "When were cotton fibres first used?",
  "response": "Cotton fibers have been used for thousands of years, with the earliest evidence of their use dating back to around 5000 BCE. Archaeological findings suggest that cotton was independently domesticated in different regions, including the Indus Valley in present-day Pakistan and India, and regions in the Americas such as Peru. These early uses of cotton show that ancient civilizations recognized the utility of cotton fibers for making textiles and garments long before modern history.",
